In 1993, when I was 12 years old, this is the guy that gave me my first bass guitar. 30 years later I’m still grateful for this guy giving me a start to what will become my life’s journey. Happy Birthday Shelton Cole.

As we are coming to an end of 2023 I wanted to share this post. Back during the pandemic when there where no gigs going on, I took that time to find new ways of making money and start taking advantage of the extra time that I had at home. I always wanted to get into composing music for TV but did not have any connections and resources to get started. So I started to network at events like the PMC online and educating myself. I started to build up relationships with different publishers and eventually started supplying them with music. Making demanding schedules for myself and sometimes spending upwards of 12 hours just in the studio working on cues that where being asked from me. Fast forward to just 3 years later I've been over achieving my goals that I thought was not possible. Working on multiple TV shows and sometimes working on different TV shows at the same time in one day. Building up a consistent schedule and making sure I'm doing my best to put 100% in everyday. Throughout these 3 years I'm fortunate to work with companies and people such as Humans Win, Sync Stories, Key of E Music, Music Mind, 4 Elements Music. I've learned that there is not one person that can make this happen but a team of people all working together. These are just a few shows that I have gotten placements on but I'm still pretty new in this TV sync world. I'm looking forward to 2024. Let 2024 be your best year as well. Happy New Year.
Tonight at the Baked Potato jazz club. Looking forward to sharing stage with these musicians.
